1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new index for efficient text searching in highly repetitive texts, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the space and time complexity of the proposed index and compares it with existing indexes, which is a topic of interest in computational complexity. 
3. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper discusses efficient pattern matching and text searching, which are important topics in information retrieval. 
4. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves the use of mathematical concepts and techniques, such as the Burrows-Wheeler Transform and Lempel-Ziv parse, which are relevant to discrete mathematics. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The proposed index can be applied to various fields, such as genomics and software repositories, which fall under the scope of computational engineering, finance, and science.
